<HEADLINE>
FT  06 APR 93 / Management (The Growing Business): Learning a degree of
management skill - In a Nutshell
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Open University (OU) has launched a Certificate in Small Business
Management to help owners, managers and advisers improve their management
and business planning skills.
The certificate can be obtained through two five-month courses covering Core
Skills in Small Business Management and Focus on Growth, each costing Pounds
450.
The OU has completed regional trials of the scheme and is now running a
national pilot programme to cater further to the needs of business and other
vocational qualification schemes. The pilot programme is being managed
jointly with local Training and Enterprise Councils and chambers of
commerce.
Contact Jayne Usher, Customer Service Centre, The Open University, Walton
Hall, Milton Keynes, MK7 6YY. Tel: 0908 653473.
