<HEADLINE>
FT  06 APR 93 / Tax set to rise, highest for four years
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
TAXATION as a proportion of national income is set to rise this year to the
highest level for four years, the free-market Adam Smith Institute says.
The proportion will rise this year to 41.68 per cent from 39.43 per cent
last year and 42.18 per cent in 1989 - itself the highest since 1985 when it
was 42.35 per cent.
It says the change is 'deeply disturbing' - after the early 1980s, when tax
as a proportion of national income fell, Britain 'is once more becoming a
high tax economy'.
