<HEADLINE>
FT  06 APR 93 / High Court calls eating-up time
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
RESTAURANTS ARE entitled to give customers 'eating-up time' in the same way
that public houses can give drinking-up time, the High Court ruled
yesterday.
Southampton magistrates found Mr Anwar Amin guilty of contravening a
condition of his restaurant licence which prevented him from 'keeping open'
between 3am and 5am. Mr Amin admitted that some customers were still eating
at 3.45am when police officers visited the restaurant. But no customers were
admitted after 3am, and diners were finishing their meals, he argued.
Allowing an appeal, Mr Justice Rougier, sitting with Lord Justice Watkins,
said customers in the restaurant at 3am were entitled to finish their meals.
