<HEADLINE>
FT  05 APR 93 / Pay awards 'lifted by merit schemes'
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Employers who linked rises to merit increased their pay bill by 5 per cent
last year compared with a 4.5 per cent increase for those giving general
increases, a survey of 1,100 settlements by independent pay analyst
Industrial Relations Services has found.
Pay freezes and deferrals were less common among merit-pay employers, it
said.
IRS data showed average pay settlements for the three months to the end of
February at a new low of 3 per cent, compared with 3.6 per cent at the end
of December.
</TEXT>
