   BERLIN, BONN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
IG Metall, Germany's big engineering union, has called for nationwide
protests from April 24 in support of higher wage demands by eastern
Germany's electrical, metal and steel sectors.
Mr Franz Steinkuhler, head of the unon, also told a rally in the east German
city of Magdeburg at the weekend that members throughout the five east
German states would be balloted later this month on whether to hold an
all-out strike in the region. He added that IG Metall would continue warning
