German levels. The employers say they cannot now meet the demands because of
the recession in western Germany and low productivity in the east.
Mr Klaus Topfer, Germany's federal environment minister, arrived in
Bucharest yesterday to assess ways to clean up 400 tonnes of toxic waste
illegally exported by German companies to Romania in recent years, writes
Ariane Genillard in Bonn.
The waste, exported by both east and west German companies, has been stored
in and around the Transylvanian town of Sibiu in coroding containers,
according to Greenpeace.
Mr Topfer is expected to sign a co-operation agreement with Romanian
officials during his two-day visit.
