<HEADLINE>
FT  03 APR 93 / UK Company News: Public support for Holiday Chemical
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The offer to the public of shares in Holliday Chemical Holdings was
subscribed 2.4 times. Some 10.2m shares were under offer and applications
were received for 24m with a total value of almost Pounds 50m.
Applications for 250 and 500 shares will be met in full; for 750, 1,000 and
1,500 the allocation is 500; those seeking 2,000 and 2,500 will receive 750;
for 3,000 and 3,500 the return is 1,000; and applications for 4,000, 4,500
and 5,000 come away with 1,500 shares.
For applications of more than 5,000 the allocation will be about 32 per
cent.
The 10.2m shares were the clawback element in a total of 40.7m shares,
valued at Pounds 79.4m at the issue price of 195p, placed with institutional
and other investors.
Allotment letters are expected to be posted next Wednesday, and dealings to
start the following day.
</TEXT>
