<HEADLINE>
FT  03 APR 93 / Phillips &amp; Drew name dropped
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE NAME Phillips &amp; Drew, once one of the strongest brand names in the UK
stockbroking business, has been dropped by UBS, the London-based investment
banking arm of Union Bank of Switzerland which took over the broker at the
time of Big Bang in 1986, Richard Waters writes.
Mr Rudi Mueller, head of UBS in London, called the move a 'logical
extension' of the integration of P&amp;D with the former UBS Securities
business.
The name will live on for a short while in Phillips &amp; Drew Fund Management,
one of the leading pension fund managers in the UK, although here too it is
expected to be dropped after a period.
</TEXT>
