FT  03 APR 93 / International Company News: US carrier seeks Heathrow route
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
AMERICAN Airlines yesterday said it had asked the US Department of
Transportation for authority to operate the route between Philadelphia and
London's Heathrow airport, writes Nikki Tait in New York. The authority is
being sold by USAir as part of its tie-up with British Airways.
Earlier in the week, another US carrier, United Airlines, had offered to buy
the authority from USAir for Dollars 14.5m.
