<HEADLINE>
FT  03 APR 93 / Bank of Japan engages in intervention in foreign exchange
market
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TOKYO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE Bank of Japan, the country's central bank, engaged in long-awaited
intervention in the foreign exchange market in Tokyo yesterday, Reuter
reports from Tokyo.
It persistently bought US dollars below Y114 in afternoon trading. Earlier
in the day it bought a small amount of dollars at around Y113.85 through
several Japanese banks and a few foreign banks, after the US currency had
hit an historic low of Y113.5 in mid-morning trade.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
