<HEADLINE>
FT  03 APR 93 / Finance &amp; The Family: Top annuity rates
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
ANNUITY rates rose slightly last month. According to the Annuity Bureau
(11-12 Hanover Square, London, W1R 9BD, tel: 071-495 1495), which produces
the table, Generali has raised its rates by 1 per cent and Royal Life by 2
per cent in the past week. This follows an increase in long gilt yields.
Life expectancy is the other determinant of annuity rates, and a few
companies will 'underwrite' an annuity if medical evidence shows that your
life expectancy is reduced. According to Billy Burrows, of Annuity Direct,
two companies, Sun Life and Providence Capitol, lead the market, while
Prudential and Norwich Union will underwrite an annuity on request. This is
done by adding notionally to the number of years - usually up to a maximum
of 10 - you have lived already and giving an annuity on this basis.
