<TEXT>
I AM 65 years and my gross income is above Pounds 14,200, the higher
personal / married man's allowance for this age.
My wife and I have joint holding of gilts. We share the income. If I arrange
for the whole gross income to go to my wife I can reduce my income to Pounds
14,200 gross. Is this allowed or must I sell the joint holding and
repurchase in my wife's name? My wife is 63 and still working. Both our
basic personal allowances (Pounds 3,445) are used up. As well as having the
interest paid into an account in your wife's sole name (to which you have no
access), you would have to transfer the stock into her sole name. Ask your
tax office for the free pamphlet IR68 (Accrued-income scheme). The phone
number of the Bonds and Stocks Office (Blackpool, FY3 9YP) is 0253-697333.
